{
  "stem": "14897.5",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So you-- who knows what I would have been like if it wasn't for the Holocaust?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Maybe a better person, maybe not-- probably a more shallow person.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know, it-- it-- surviving doesn't qualify you for understanding the Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Even though you have experienced it, it doesn't mean that you have necessarily a deeper understanding of it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But perhaps it makes you think about it more later, when-- when you are an adult and you sort of can't help but review these events.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I have an analytical mind.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I always try to understand things.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I try to think and understand how such an event could have happened.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't have the answers.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Nobody has, of course.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And you know, if you think about it, either way, either you think that there are some peoples who are capable of such deeds, who are predisposed to such deeds, or if you think that everybody is capable of it given a certain history and a certain set of circumstances, I don't know what's worse.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Which way it is-- to think about it is worse?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I-- I do think that even if there are some people predisposed, or peoples, it comes out if they feel aggrieved and humiliated.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Happy people don't go around murdering other people.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "As time goes on, I am tending to think in more universal terms about it because small holocausts have happened since, and they have happened in various parts of the world.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You almost have to think that there is something in the human nature.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It's-- no matter how you think about it, you cannot help but be pessimistic about the fact that this can always crop up given certain history and circumstances.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
